Here's a basic C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the occurrences of a specific word. 

Please make sure to replace "specific_word" in the code with the actual word you want to count:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::ifstream file("filename.txt"); // Replace "filename.txt" with your file name
    std::string specific_word = "specific_word"; // Replace "specific_word" with your specific word

    if (file.is_open()) {
        std::string line;
        int word_count = 0;

        while (std::getline(file, line)) {
            std::string::size_type pos = 0;
            std::string::size_type word_start = 0;
            std::string::size_type word_end = 0;

            while ((word_start = line.find_first_not_of(" \n\t", pos)) != std::string::npos) {
                word_end = line.find_first_of(" \n\t", word_start);
                std::string word = line.substr(word_start, word_end - word_start);
                if (word == specific_word) {
                    word_count++;
                }
                pos = word_end;
            }
        }

        file.close();
        std::cout << "The number of occurrences of the specific word is: " << word_count << std::endl;
    } else {
        std::cout << "Unable to open file." << std::endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
```

This program starts by opening the text file you specify. If the file is successfully opened, it then reads the file line by line. For each line, it searches for the specific word by finding the first character that is not a whitespace character (space, newline, or tab) and then finds the end of the word by finding the first whitespace character after the start of the word. If a match is found, it increments the count of occurrences. Finally, it prints out the number of occurrences of the specific word in the file.
